The paper deals with unsupervised feature learning approaches for medical images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning approaches (cs.LG) and generative adversarial networks (cs.MM) for this task. Additionally, the paper mentions the possibility of using these methods for medical information retrieval problems (cs.CL).
